##Britain's 'quarantine' diary | March 15: I spray three alcohol sprays on take-out bags

One

Today, learn to write in the article before the first light a scented candle.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fantastic scented herbal tea. Many people may not accept it.

A different kind of herbal tea at night, The Noir Parfume Auguste, Fauchon. It's amazing how fragrant it is. When the tea box was opened, the room was filled with the rich, sweet smell of powdered petals and apples that had grown out of nowhere. In the list of ingredients, except for black tea from China, all three come from flowers: Rose Buds, rose petals and red flower petals.

I want to reiterate what I said yesterday: I don't like herbal tea. The most enjoyable tea experience of the day is in the afternoon, when the London Sun through the French window cover the whole room, sitting in front of the window on a pot of daffodils, or a pot of Dianhong. Traditional Chinese Oolong tea and Black Tea have a strange calming effect. I would like to believe that this is a psychological effect based on traditional culture: In my perhaps some orientalist imagination, the Chinese way of drinking tea is necessarily elegant and peaceful. "Yangguan Sandie" or "Wolong Yin" in the Zheng Zheng Guqin, with a calm and indifferent heart for the most cold thinking.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
I recommend the Zither Club.

Don't laugh. I really learned to play the Guqin. Although I do not understand, but the effect of the crowd, there is a soothing effect.

Two

This afternoon was a little different, because I didn't finish my Yunnan red.

My best friend WHO's freaking out about roommate had a meltdown today. She was prone to anxiety, and her roommate's indifference made her both cold and angry. I said to her, you should be angry with him, some people are just spoiled from childhood, arrogant. Just give him a piece of your mind. She said she still has to live with the Weirdo until the second half of the year, and she doesn't want to let off steam by making the next six months harder for her.

Remembering that I would be back in April, I said to her, you can come and stay with me. She readily agreed. Nice working with you. I don't do polite. I figured I'd take some of the pressure off the top of her head.

She's in London doing an online campaign for a milk tea shop. Many of the beautiful photos you see on social media are of her holding a couple of large cups of milk tea in the next room at Pret a Manger. Although some sorry this Pret, but they are also for the development of peer contribution, give them a consolation prize.

I support her work by ordering three cups of milk tea on London's Chinese takeaway APP.

Three

To be honest, I was a little hesitant before I placed the order. I've been isolated for 12 days, and although I've been to the supermarket three times, I have no idea what the world is like outside of one stop. Is there a risk of infection if we order takeout now? But on second thought, even if there is a risk I also have a way to deal with, they chose three cups of tea, under the order. In London, take-out from tea shops is generally subject to a minimum consumption limit, which usually requires at least three cups of milk tea. This store is no exception. I flow (also do not know is happy or painful) tears, chose a cup of hot and two cups of cold.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ignoring my profile picture... I've actually been home for 12 days.

As I opened the door for takeout, I hovered sideways, sucked on the plastic bag, said a quick "thank you" and hurried to close the door. I left a plastic bag filled with three cups of milk tea on the floor in Entryway, rushed to the bathroom without looking back, and washed my hands carefully enough to sing happy birthday at least three times. Boris should give me a medal.

After washing, drying and rubbing alcohol on his hands, he went into the living room, picked up the alcohol spray, and approached the plastic bag lying on its back in Entryway awaiting trial. Don't worry. The bags are buckled, so the spray won't get to the milk tea. I was about a meter high above the plastic bag, squeeze the trigger three times with all my strength, watching the water mist like snow, like drizzle evenly fell on the plastic bag, moistening every inch of its skin. Satisfied, I turned around and went back to my room, sat down at my computer, opened my paper, and played happily on my phone for another five minutes.

After five minutes, I thought I had enough, pulled out two sheets of toilet paper, went to Entryway, opened the plastic bag, used the paper to bring three cups of milk tea and a straw into the house, then rushed into the bathroom and washed my hands.

By the time I got to the milk tea, the only hot drink had gone cold, and the two cold drinks were becoming room temperature.

Four

In the end, these three cups of milk tea could not be wiped out by me. I will be left with a cup of frozen in the refrigerator, ready to drink tomorrow, but I do not know drinking tea will not affect the stomach overnight. Think of two months ago, I also countless greedy, a person at home but want to order milk tea take-out, watching the minimum consumption of three cups of milk tea is prohibitive. If I had a girlfriend, it would make the decision a lot easier.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The Cup of milk tea that I've frozen..

Single people have single problems, and couples have couple problems. My CASS Business School friend is not going to America. With less than two days to go until trump closes the border with the United States, the last few airports in the United States that still receive flights from Britain and Ireland are full. The Gateway to Customs "the gateway to all men" -- "Forex" -- is in quotation marks because it is said to be an ungainly term for customs, with a maximum waiting time of up to six hours.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
To make matters worse, none of the customs officers wore masks, and few of the tourists lining up wore them.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
A giant Petri dish.

Her boyfriend, who had planned to visit Britain in early March, was delayed by the outbreak. Now, in a twist, she will not be able to travel to the United States to meet him. It's a sad story, but it's not for outsiders anymore.

Five

Our school has actually been on strike for the past four weeks and is not in session. Tomorrow was supposed to be the first day of classes after the strike (and the last two weeks of my undergraduate career) , but the epidemic prevented me from going to school.

The teacher sent an E-mail, advance notice that this is his first online class, really do not know how to operate, to prepare for the class can not. Bubble in the paper Ocean I did not read a reading, did not want to have a class in the first place, then silently pray that the teacher not too fast to learn how to operate.

The week is over. It's a new week and I'm not looking forward to it. After all, we don't know what tomorrow will bring.
